(Tim Moore) writes:
|> In article <aZHZVB15w165w@mantis.co.uk> mathew <mathew@mantis.co.uk>
|> writes:
|> >  PGP does not use any techniques which are patented in the EC.
|> 
|> The IDEA cipher is patented in Switzerland.  I admit that I don't
|> know if Switzerland is considered part of the EC or not.

Switzerland is NOT part of the EC at the present time.  Switzerland
is not even a member of the EES (European Economic Space).  However,
note that international patents for IDEA are pending.

Disclaimer:  Even though I happen to be employed by the institution
where IDEA was developed, I have had nothing to do with it.

